 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Spatial Spectrum"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "from spatial_spectrum import SpatialSpectrum"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Load Data \n",
    "The simulated raw radar IF signals.\n",
    "20 Tx * 20 Rx, one chirp, 256 samples per chirp.  (Vayyar TrigB radar)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "torch.Size([20, 20, 1, 256])\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sig = np.load(\"data/human_sig.npy\")\n",
    "sig=torch.tensor(sig,requires_grad=True,device='cuda')\n",
    "print(sig.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Process Spatial Spectrum"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "SpatialSpectrumGen= SpatialSpectrum()\n",
    "spect3D = SpatialSpectrumGen.radar_image(sig)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Visualization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.colorbar.Colorbar at 0x7f69c43259d0>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "image =spect3D.sum(dim=2).cpu()\n",
    "plt.imshow(np.rot90(20 * torch.log10(torch.abs(image).detach().cpu()),3))\n",
    "plt.colorbar()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Backpropagation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "loss = torch.sum(torch.abs(spect3D))\n",
    "loss.backward()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Normally, the gradient can be backpropagated through the spatial spectrum algorithm.\n",
    "\n",
    "But the local non-convexity problem still exist, so we developed a spatial spectrum surrogate"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
